ications for policy reforms aimed at ameliorating the community effects of mass incarceration and promoting alternatives to the carceral system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aImprisonmentxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aPrisonsxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aSegregationzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520380349zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520380349423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520380349/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSLb2021